    (
      gen_random_uuid(),
      'Explain the CSS box model. What is the difference between ''box-sizing: content-box'' and ''box-sizing: border-box''?',
      'Box model understanding is fundamental. Explain how box-sizing affects width and height calculations.',
      'multiple-choice',
      'intermediate',
      15,
      '[{"id":"o1","text":"content-box: width excludes padding/border; border-box: width includes padding/border","isCorrect":true,"explanation":"Correct. This is how box-sizing works."},{"id":"o2","text":"They are identical","isCorrect":false,"explanation":"Incorrect. They calculate width differently."},{"id":"o3","text":"content-box is deprecated","isCorrect":false,"explanation":"Incorrect. Both are valid, just different behaviors."},{"id":"o4","text":"border-box excludes padding from width","isCorrect":false,"explanation":"Incorrect. border-box includes padding and border in width."}]',
      'content-box: width excludes padding/border; border-box: width includes padding/border',
      'content-box: width/height = content only (padding/border add to total). border-box: width/height = content + padding + border (total size matches specified). border-box is more intuitive and commonly used in modern CSS.',
      NULL,
