      'Which CSS selectors have the highest specificity? (Select all that apply)',
      'Understanding selector specificity helps resolve style conflicts. Identify the highest specificity selectors.',
      'multiple-select',
      'intermediate',
      15,
      '[{"id":"o1","text":"Inline styles (style attribute)","isCorrect":true,"explanation":"Correct. Inline styles have highest specificity."},{"id":"o2","text":"ID selectors (<code>#id</code>)","isCorrect":true,"explanation":"Correct. IDs have high specificity (100)."},{"id":"o3","text":"Class selectors (<code>.class</code>)","isCorrect":false,"explanation":"Incorrect. Classes have lower specificity (10) than IDs."},{"id":"o4","text":"Element selectors (div)","isCorrect":false,"explanation":"Incorrect. Elements have lowest specificity (1)."}]',
      'Inline styles (style attribute)',
      'Inline styles (style=''...'') have highest specificity (1000). IDs (<code>#id</code>) have 100. Classes (<code>.class</code>), attributes (<code>[attr]</code>), and pseudo-classes (<code>:hover</code>) have 10. Elements (div) and pseudo-elements (<code>::before</code>) have 1.',
      NULL,
