      '096e44e0-d3a5-4263-81ae-afebd3b70833',
      300
    ),
    (
      gen_random_uuid(),
      'What is the purpose of the ''defer'' and ''async'' attributes on <script> tags, and when should each be used?',
      'As a senior developer optimizing page load performance, explain the differences between defer, async, and neither attribute on script tags, including execution order and DOM readiness.',
      'multiple-choice',
      'intermediate',
      15,
      '[{"id":"o1","text":"''async'' executes as soon as downloaded (order not guaranteed); ''defer'' executes after HTML parsing in document order","isCorrect":true,"explanation":"Correct. ''async'' prioritizes speed but loses execution order. ''defer'' maintains order and waits for DOM."},{"id":"o2","text":"Both ''async'' and ''defer'' execute scripts in the same order they appear in the document","isCorrect":false,"explanation":"Incorrect. ''async'' scripts execute as soon as they''re downloaded, which may not match document order."},{"id":"o3","text":"''defer'' blocks HTML parsing, ''async'' does not","isCorrect":false,"explanation":"Incorrect. Both allow parallel downloading. Neither blocks parsing, but scripts without attributes do block parsing."},{"id":"o4","text":"''async'' and ''defer'' are identical in behavior, just different syntax","isCorrect":false,"explanation":"Incorrect. They have fundamentally different execution timing and ordering guarantees."}]',
      '''async'' executes as soon as downloaded (order not guaranteed); ''defer'' executes after HTML parsing in document order',
      'Without attributes: script blocks HTML parsing. ''async'': downloads in parallel, executes immediately when ready (order not guaranteed). ''defer'': downloads in parallel, executes after HTML parsing completes, in document order. Use ''async'' for independent scripts (analytics). Use ''defer'' for scripts that depend on DOM or need execution order.',
      NULL,
      ARRAY['Consider when scripts need DOM elements to be available', 'Think about dependencies between multiple scripts', 'Remember that blocking parsing affects perceived performance'],
      ARRAY['html', 'performance', 'intermediate', 'javascript'],
      '{}',
      NULL,
      '3083f50b-8a47-48a0-b100-6172cd184d04',
      NULL,
      true,
      '2025-11-18T18:46:59.282Z',
      '2025-11-18T18:46:59.282Z',
      '096e44e0-d3a5-4263-81ae-afebd3b70833',
      300
    ),
    (
      gen_random_uuid(),
      'Explain the difference between ARIA roles and native HTML5 semantic elements. When should you use each?',
      'A senior developer must understand accessibility. When should you use ARIA roles (role=''button'', role=''navigation'') vs native semantic elements (<button>, <nav>)? What are the implications?',
      'multiple-choice',
      'advanced',
      20,
      '[{"id":"o1","text":"Prefer native semantic elements; use ARIA only when native elements cannot achieve the interaction pattern","isCorrect":true,"explanation":"Correct. Native elements provide built-in accessibility features. ARIA is a fallback for custom components."},{"id":"o2","text":"ARIA roles are always better because they''re more explicit and modern","isCorrect":false,"explanation":"Incorrect. ARIA should complement, not replace, semantic HTML. Native elements provide more built-in functionality."},{"id":"o3","text":"Use ARIA roles on all interactive elements for better screen reader support","isCorrect":false,"explanation":"Incorrect. Redundant ARIA on native elements can actually confuse screen readers. Use ARIA only when necessary."},{"id":"o4","text":"Native elements and ARIA roles are equivalent, choose based on team preference","isCorrect":false,"explanation":"Incorrect. Native elements provide keyboard support, focus management, and browser behavior that ARIA alone cannot replicate."}]',
      'Prefer native semantic elements; use ARIA only when native elements cannot achieve the interaction pattern',
      'Always prefer native semantic HTML elements (<button>, <nav>, <main>) over ARIA roles because native elements provide built-in keyboard support, focus management, and browser behavior. Use ARIA roles only when native elements cannot achieve the desired interaction pattern (e.g., complex widgets, custom components). ARIA should enhance, not replace, semantic HTML.',
      NULL,
      ARRAY['Consider what built-in behaviors native elements provide (keyboard, focus, etc.)', 'Think about the ''no ARIA is better than bad ARIA'' principle', 'Remember that ARIA enhances, not replaces, semantic HTML'],
      ARRAY['html', 'accessibility', 'aria', 'difficult', 'semantic-html'],
