    ),
    (
      gen_random_uuid(),
      'What is the difference between <meta name=''viewport''> and <meta http-equiv=''X-UA-Compatible''>? Explain their impact on rendering.',
      'Senior developers need to understand how meta tags affect browser rendering. Explain these two meta tags and when each is necessary.',
      'multiple-choice',
      'intermediate',
      15,
      '[{"id":"o1","text":"Viewport controls mobile responsive rendering; X-UA-Compatible forces IE/Edge rendering engine version","isCorrect":true,"explanation":"Correct. Viewport is for responsive design on mobile devices. X-UA-Compatible is for legacy IE compatibility."},{"id":"o2","text":"Both control the same thing but for different browsers","isCorrect":false,"explanation":"Incorrect. They serve completely different purposes: viewport for responsive design, X-UA-Compatible for IE compatibility mode."},{"id":"o3","text":"X-UA-Compatible is required for all modern browsers to render correctly","isCorrect":false,"explanation":"Incorrect. X-UA-Compatible is only needed for legacy IE/Edge compatibility. Modern browsers don''t need it."},{"id":"o4","text":"Viewport is optional and only affects desktop browsers","isCorrect":false,"explanation":"Incorrect. Viewport is essential for mobile responsive design and affects how mobile browsers render pages."}]',
      'Viewport controls mobile responsive rendering; X-UA-Compatible forces IE/Edge rendering engine version',
      '<meta name=''viewport''> controls mobile rendering, setting initial scale and width (e.g., width=device-width, initial-scale=1). <meta http-equiv=''X-UA-Compatible''> forces IE/Edge to use a specific rendering engine version (e.g., IE=edge). Viewport is essential for responsive design. X-UA-Compatible is legacy for IE compatibility.',
      NULL,
      ARRAY['Consider which browsers need X-UA-Compatible', 'Think about what ''responsive design'' means for mobile devices', 'Remember that modern browsers have different requirements than legacy IE'],
      ARRAY['html', 'meta-tags', 'responsive', 'intermediate', 'browser-compatibility'],
