      300
    ),
    (
      gen_random_uuid(),
      'What is the difference between <iframe sandbox> and regular <iframe>? What security restrictions does sandbox enforce?',
      'Senior developers must understand iframe security. Explain sandbox attribute restrictions and when to use it.',
      'multiple-choice',
      'advanced',
      20,
      '[{"id":"o1","text":"Sandbox blocks scripts, forms, popups by default; tokens like ''allow-scripts'' can selectively enable features","isCorrect":true,"explanation":"Correct. Sandbox is a security feature that restricts iframe capabilities, with opt-in tokens for specific features."},{"id":"o2","text":"Sandbox and regular iframe have identical security properties","isCorrect":false,"explanation":"Incorrect. Sandbox applies strict restrictions that regular iframes don''t have."},{"id":"o3","text":"Sandbox allows all features by default, you disable them with tokens","isCorrect":false,"explanation":"Incorrect. Sandbox blocks everything by default and requires explicit tokens to allow features."},{"id":"o4","text":"Sandbox is only for styling purposes, not security","isCorrect":false,"explanation":"Incorrect. Sandbox is specifically a security feature to isolate untrusted content."}]',
      'Sandbox blocks scripts, forms, popups by default; tokens like ''allow-scripts'' can selectively enable features',
      '<iframe sandbox> applies strict security restrictions: blocks scripts, forms, popups, plugins, and top-level navigation by default. You can selectively allow features with tokens like ''allow-scripts'', ''allow-forms'', ''allow-same-origin''. Regular <iframe> has no such restrictions. Use sandbox for untrusted content (user-generated, third-party widgets).',
      NULL,
      ARRAY['Think about what ''sandbox'' means in security contexts', 'Consider the principle of least privilege', 'Remember that untrusted content needs isolation'],
      ARRAY['html', 'security', 'iframe', 'sandbox', 'difficult'],
      '{}',
      NULL,
      '3083f50b-8a47-48a0-b100-6172cd184d04',
      NULL,
      true,
