</code></pre>

React Suspense is a built-in feature that lets you defer rendering part of your component tree until some condition(asynchronous operation) is metusually, data or code has finished loading. While waiting, Suspense lets you display a fallback UI like a spinner or placeholder.


     1. Lazy loading components uses suspense feature,


        If the module containing the dynamic import is not yet loaded by the time parent component renders, you must show some fallback content while youre waiting for it to load using a loading indicator. This can be done using **Suspense** component.
    
        The above component shows fallback UI instead real component until `OtherComponent` is fully loaded.

     2. As an another example, suspend until async data(data fetching) is ready',
